in security plans, procedures, and other documentation as required. Investigate new platforms and tools throughout the industry and make recommendations for their use in current and future projects Advise management through the creation of scorecards and reporting that display our risk profile and provide insight for decision making. Provide proactive analysis and options for systems and operations changes to implement regulatory requirements from CMS (Center for Medicaid Services) regarding the system. Contact customer when new CMS rules (draft and final) are released, organizing meetings to present the results and help to provide comments for CMS and propose solutions to implement the rules (controls) in the system. To learn more about us visit us at https://www.ibm.com/watson-health/government #govhhs Required Technical and Professional Expertise 5+ years of IT (information technology) related experience 3+ years of related IT security 3+ years of IT leadership experience Healthcare IT Background Security or control related certification (e.g., CISSP, CISM, CISA). Experience with external audits including FedRAMP, SSAE18, MITA, etc Experience with the HIPAA Security and Privacy rules and NIST SP 800-53 controls including application/implementation of controls in production environments. Understanding of infrastructure control procedures and security (networking, OS, storage, application) Ability to present information clearly and concisely to customers, management, and other non-technical stakeholders Preferred Technical and Professional Expertise Healthcare IT experience Knowledge and understanding of data warehouse solution architecture including DBMS, Data Management, BI, Analytics, etc. About Business Unit IBM\u2019s Industry Consultants are essential to our clients as they work to reinvent themselves for the future. Join our highly visible and highly skilled team of global consultants as we strive to accelerate sales, deliver client engagements, and build IB